A vast underground root system of an ancient tree transforms midway into glowing interconnected neural pathways and mycelium networks, viewed from a cross-section perspective. The upper portion shows a traditional oak tree with rigid branching structure in muted earth tones, while below the soil line the roots gradually morph into an organic web of bioluminescent connections in soft blues and greens, spreading horizontally in all directions rather than following hierarchical patterns. Tiny nodes pulse where connections meet, suggesting living information exchange. The style evokes Studio Ghibli's organic magical realism with soft watercolor textures, dreamy atmosphere, and a sense of wonder at natural systems. Warm golden sunlight filters from above while the underground network glows with its own inner light, creating a beautiful contrast between the structured visible world and the chaotic-yet-functional hidden connections beneath.
